  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The rationale of this study was to evaluate the efficacy of Axiostat hemostatic dental
      dressing in achieving hemostasis post-extraction and determining its effect on pain and
      healing of the extraction wound, compared to control, i.e. conventional method of extraction
      in patients on oral anti-platelet therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
